**Salary sacrifice to superannuation** lets you divert pre-tax salary into your super fund, where it is taxed at only 15% (concessional contributions tax) instead of your marginal rate. For someone in the 32% bracket (30% + 2% Medicare), every $10,000 sacrificed saves approximately **$1,700 in tax** compared to receiving it as income.

The concessional contributions cap is **$30,000 per year** — including your employer's SG contributions. On a $100,000 salary with $12,000 SG, you have room to sacrifice up to $18,000 more within the cap.
